POLICE need help to identify the body of a man who was shot and killed in Bekkersdal, west of Joburg. The man, believed to be in his 20s, was wearing black jeans and a striped blue and green jersey when he was killed over the weekend. Police spokeswoman Sergeant Linkie Lefakane said: “According to our investigations, residents found a man with multiple injuries lying on his back. “We need the community’s help to find his next of kin.” Lefakane said police were investigating a case of murder. “No arrests have been made yet.” Anyone with information that could assist police can contact Bekkersdal cop shop on 011 755 8040, Crime Stop on 08600 10111, or investigating officer Constable Moeketsi Maoba on 072 561 9417.